Description: Lower body sherd of large Chian, possibly Mature Animal Style, pottery chalice; white slip; interior glazed streaky black with two faded added white bands; exterior: end of two vertical lines, possibly part of handle frill pattern; below, a band, with a second band near bottom of sherd; inscription on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0438) (phase 2)
